  <p class="specs">Weight: 10.0 oz &bull; Cushion: Low &bull; Cut: Low &bull; Surface: Indoor Court &bull; Play Style: Speed/Slashing</p>
  <p>The Nike G.T. Cut 4 is the most advanced basketball shoe Nike has ever built for guards and slashers — a low-top, court-feel masterpiece engineered for the modern multidimensional player. Unveiled when Paige Bueckers wore it during the 2025 WNBA All-Star Weekend, the G.T. Cut 4 combines ZoomX 3.0 foam with a parabolic Zoom Strobel for unprecedented cushioning responsiveness in a basketball shoe. RBR-X foam adds lateral stability during cuts, and a Cushlon carrier provides structural support. The generative traction pattern was specifically designed for multi-directional cuts and quick changes of direction. A 3D-molded exoskeleton upper provides containment without bulk. Available starting January 2026. Best for: guards, wings, and any player whose game is built around quickness, cutting, and lateral movement. Key specs: ZoomX 3.0 + Zoom Strobel + RBR-X, 10.0 oz (W), low cut, speed/slashing, indoor court.</p>
  
</div>

